&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Website:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.greenworkstools.com&quot;&gt;www.greenworkstools.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Company Summary:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenworks Tools is a leader in battery-powered outdoor power equipment, designing and manufacturing innovative products that deliver professional-grade performance—without the fumes, noise, or environmental impact of gas-powered alternatives. As the industry leader in battery-powered outdoor power equipment (OPE), Greenworks proudly serves both DIY consumers and landscaping professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our growing product portfolio includes residential and commercial riding mowers, off-road utility vehicles, side-by-sides, and more. With best-in-class battery, control, and drive technologies, we offer the right tool for every job—powered responsibly.&amp;nbsp; Join a company that’s shaping a cleaner, more sustainable future. We’re looking for motivated, detail-oriented professionals who thrive in a fast-paced manufacturing environment and are passionate about quality, teamwork, accuracy, and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory Control Specialist is responsible for maintaining accurate inventory records, supporting warehouse operations, and ensuring inventory integrity across all warehouse locations. This position works closely with receiving, warehouse, production, shipping, planning, purchasing, and finance teams to investigate inventory discrepancies and improve inventory-related processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is detail-oriented, organized, process-driven, and capable of working effectively in a fast-paced manufacturing and warehouse environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inventory Accuracy &amp;amp; Cycle Counts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily, weekly, and monthly cycle counts based on ABC inventory classifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve discrepancies between physical inventory and system inventory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate inventory records within ERP systems (TipTop/SAP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research inventory variances and determine root causes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory transactions for errors or abnormal activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support inventory adjustments with proper documentation and required approvals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Warehouse &amp;amp; Inventory Control Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized warehouse locations with proper inventory labeling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure materials are stored in correct locations and accurately identified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the implementation and maintenance of warehouse location systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support warehouse cleanliness and inventory organization initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help prevent material loss, misplacement, and inventory damage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Material Handler&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
