&lt;p&gt;This position provides hands-on leadership to quality inspectors while partnering cross-functionally to improve processes, resolve issues, and strengthen overall product performance. You’ll have a direct impact on operational efficiency, customer satisfaction, and continuous quality improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and train a team of quality inspectors to ensure high performance and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor team productivity and adjust priorities to meet operational demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Quality Manager to identify and implement process improvements that enhance efficiency and product quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the proper daily use, inspection, and maintenance of measuring instruments and tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direct quality support to Product Management and Engineering to resolve customer issues and product returns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key liaison between Service, Manufacturing, Engineering, Product, and Sales teams to drive continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support quality control activities for incoming materials, in-process production, and finished goods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile and analyze daily quality data, identifying trends and leading root cause analysis for nonconformities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other related duties as needed to support departmental and company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
