&lt;p&gt;As a rapidly growing global manufacturer of residential and commercial products, Greenworks is leading the charge toward a more powerful and sustainable future. With over 20 years of research and development, including over 1000 patents in outdoor power equipment, power tools, and lifestyle products, we’re pushing the limits of what battery technology can do to improve the quality of work and life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Quality Inspector is responsible for ensuring that the product produced meets our company quality standards by utilizing a variety of testing equipment. This role will also inspect incoming materials from our suppliers to ensure they meet all specifications and quality standards. This role will also work with the production team to ensure all parts and products meet quality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the function of instrument use and the quality standards for incoming materials, internal materials, and end of line products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize various instruments to perform quality assurance tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that production team is following Standard Operating Procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit and monitor quality requirements in accordance with company specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily maintenance of test equipment and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and report test results. Monitor any nonconformances and initiate corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain data accuracy in reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify issues and research root causes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up the corrective actions and verify if it’s effective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conditionally improve the test tooling instruments and improve the accuracy of the quality tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complies with established policies and safety practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs all other duties as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Required Education and Experience:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HS Diploma/GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years manufacturing experience required. (1 or more years in quality preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have basic knowledge of electronics and machinery, be able to understand the basic operation and principles of testing have the ability to apply knowledge to new products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to read and interpret specifications and part prints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills, both verbal and written.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Compensation and Benefits:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, dental, and vision coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assistance with fertility treatment and adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k company match plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid sick, vacation time, and company holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
